headline: 'My Brother Is My Family Also': Husband Asks Wife To Return To Work So He Can Pay For Brother's College
summary: A man turned to Reddit's r/AmITheA**hole forum recently after clashing with his wife about finances and family priorities. He said he asked his wife to return to work so he could help his younger brother pay for college. The post quickly drew thousands of comments and votes, sparking a debate about marriage, caregiving, and obligations to extended family. The husband explained his brother cared for their mother with dementia for six years after their father died. Brother Put Life On Hold The Red
